---
description: Use Headroom MCP tools to compress large context before analysis
alwaysApply: true
---

When working with large content, use the Headroom MCP tools to save context tokens:

- Before analyzing file contents over 500 lines, long grep/search output, build logs, or JSON dumps, call `headroom_compress` on the raw text first.
- Work from the compressed result; use `headroom_retrieve` with the returned hash when you need the original full content or to search within it.
- After long sessions with multiple compressions, call `headroom_stats` to report token savings.

Do not skip compression for very large tool outputs when Headroom MCP is available.
